GPS-Garmin-Connect

GPS::Garmin::Connect is a simple module which allows you to fetch your
activities from http://connect.garmin.com

WARNING: It is NOT based on any official API released by Garmin. It 
simply logs in using the web form and fetches JSON data just like 
the flash UI does. It might break at any time.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc GPS::Garmin::Connect

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=GPS-Garmin-Connect

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/GPS-Garmin-Connect

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/GPS-Garmin-Connect

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/GPS-Garmin-Connect


